 it used to do or still does along with registries. Came up with a design which is a page which will divert the three types of users of Cuddly: Pet Parents, Donors, and Rescues.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"banner_image\":\"45\",\"thumbnail\":\"44\"}','{\"details\":\"<p>poundWISHES, now CUDDLY is an online crowdfunding platform that connects animal lovers with animal rescues and shelters. Technology is at the heart of the business. Ignite Solutions (my current workplace) are the UX &amp; technology partner for CUDDLY.<\\/p>\\n<p>Our first task was to bring stabilize the existing system. poundWISHES was handled by another firm earlier and we faced a lot of issues while working with the previous architecture and hence came up with a simple one-flow-at-a-time revamp plan.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>We recommended a multi-phased UX improvement and modernizing approach. The web interface was revamped to give the site a fresh look. We established detailed web and campaign tracking to give insights into donor behavior.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>Tighter and reliable integration with payment providers reduced reconciliation errors and streamlined the crowdfunding distribution.<\\/p>\\n<p>We embarked on a major initiative to bring in an innovative pet gift registry offering, the first of its kind. Donors could gift items to rescued pets rather than just cash. This offering has been a hit.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>Working with CUDDLY to introduce new features and improvise the experience as we now have a comparatively stable system.<\\/p>\\n<p>The client wanted to highlight the new feature on the homepage \\\"adopter registries\\\" and suggested a design but it failed to make users understand what it used to do or still does along with registries. Came up with a design which is a page which will divert the three types of users of Cuddly: Pet Parents, Donors, and Rescues.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"id\":\"19\"}',NULL,NULL,1,'2018-10-17 19:08:49','192.168.0.1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (