ent_element \\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_wrapper\\\">\\n<h3 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>The Solution<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">The most critical feature was to come up the alignment interaction: a way to guide users to align the device to only one of the X, Y and Z dimensions.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">Taking a cue from airplane horizon indicators, the elegant UX solution was to align the black border (which moves with one of the dimensions), the blue line (which moves with another dimension) with the red line which indicates the perfect center.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">A similar approach was used for the horizontal plane but with overlapping bubbles.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000068.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_usage\\\" width=\\\"938\\\" height=\\\"975\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<div class=\\\"prk_shortcode-title prk_break_word pulse_left_align h3_sized\\\">\\n<p>A simple set of instructions told users what to do and vibration based feedback indicated when they had succeeded.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000067.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_instructions\\\" width=\\\"1280\\\" height=\\\"720\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<h3 class=\\\"header_font zero_color prk_vc_title\\\">The Gamification<\\/h3>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\"><span style=\\\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\\\">To motivate users to work this repeatedly and to provide enough statistical data for our experiments, we gamified the experiences and allowed users to compete against themselves in seeing how fast they could get all 6 readings done.<\\/span><\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000069.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_game\\\" width=\\\"837\\\" height=\\\"701\\\" \\/><\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\