to bring stabilize the existing system. poundWISHES was handled by another firm earlier and we faced a lot of issues while working with the previous architecture and hence came up with a simple one-flow-at-a-time revamp plan.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>We recommended a multi-phased UX improvement and modernizing approach. The web interface was revamped to give the site a fresh look. We established detailed web and campaign tracking to give insights into donor behavior.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>Tighter and reliable integration with payment providers reduced reconciliation errors and streamlined the crowdfunding distribution.<\\/p>\\n<p>We embarked on a major initiative to bring in an innovative pet gift registry offering, the first of its kind. Donors could gift items to rescued pets rather than just cash. This offering has been a hit.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>Working with CUDDLY to introduce new features and improvise the experience as we now have a comparatively stable system.<\\/p>\\n<p>The client wanted to highlight the new feature on the homepage \\\"adopter registries\\\" and suggested a design but it failed to make users understand what it used to do or still does along with registries. Came up with a design which is a page which will divert the three types of users of Cuddly: Pet Parents, Donors, and Rescues.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000075.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"homepage_cuddly\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"635\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"id\":\"19\"}',NULL,NULL,1,'2018-10-18 15:34:15','192.168.0.1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/69.0.3497.100 Safari/537.36'),(346,'ENTRY','UPDATE','25','projects',25,1,'{\"id\":\"25\",\"status\":\"1\",\"sort\":null,\"project_type_id\":\"2\",\"title\":\"Zilkr\",\"subtitle\":null,\"details\":\"<h2 class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr<\\/h2>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr builds platforms that API-enable an enterprise&rsquo;s telecom network. Requests and events in the telecom network, such as incoming calls, messages or outgoing calls, can now be integrated with Internet-based services.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000073.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Zilkr desktop\\\" width=\\\"1281\\\" height=\\\"779\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr came to Ignite to help conceptualize what such an integrated phone and desktop experience could look like. Furthermore, Zilkr wanted to explore what such an experience would require from a technology protocol perspective to allow 3rd party apps to execute in the Zilkr framework.<\\/p>\\n<p>Rather than jump into this from a UX design perspective, we applied a design thinking approach to balance the business needs of Zilkr, the user&rsquo;s expectations and intuitive interfaces and the technology protocol that would sustain such a framework for 3rd party developed apps.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000074.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Zilkr notification\\\" width=\\\"1280\\\" height=\\\"850\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>We developed a dynamic, interactive prototype that demonstrated all aspects of the user stories.<\\/p>\\n<p>Zilkr was successful in taking this interactive prototype to their customers and getting traction for a new offering.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"banner_image\":null,\"thumbnail\":\"72\"}','{\"details\":\"<h2 class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr<\\/h2>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr builds platforms that API-enable an enterprise&rsquo;s telecom network. Requests and events in the telecom network, such as incoming calls, messages or outgoing calls, can now be integrated with Internet-based services.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000073.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Zilkr desktop\\\" width=\\\"1281\\\" height=\\\"779\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Zilkr came to Ignite to help conceptualize what such an integrated phone and desktop experience could look like. Furthermore, Zilkr wanted to explore what such an experience would require from a technology protocol perspective to allow 3rd party apps to execute in the Zilkr framework.<\\/p>\\n<p>Rather than jump into this from a UX design perspective, we applied a design thinking approach to balance the business needs of Zilkr, the user&rsquo;s expectations and intuitive interfaces and the technology protocol that would sustain such a framework for 3rd party developed apps.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000074.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Zilkr notification\\\" width=\\\"1280\\\" height=\\\"850\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>We developed a dynamic, interactive prototype that demonstrated all aspects of the user stories.<\\/p>\\n<p>Zilkr was successful in taking this interactive prototype to their customers and getting traction for a new offering.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"id\":\"25\"}',NULL,NULL,1,'2018-10-18 15:35:42','192.168.0.1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/69.0.3497.100 Safari/537.36'),(347,'ENTRY','UPDATE','24','projects',24,1,'{\"id\":\"24\",\"status\":\"1\",\"sort\":null,\"project_type_id\":\"3\",\"title\":\"PhonePass\",\"subtitle\":null,\"details\":\"<div class=\\\"prk_shortcode-title prk_break_word pulse_center_align h4_sized\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"header_font zero_color prk_vc_title\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_wrapper\\\">\\n<h2 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>PhonePass<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\n<h3 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>How does one craft a User Experience for device orientations in 6 degrees of freedom?<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">PhonePass has a patent-pending algorithm to uniquely identify devices based on the hardware signature obtained by holding the device in six different very precise orientations &ndash; vertical facing you, vertical away from you, horizontal facing you, horizontal away from you, on its back, and on its face. The unique device determination is used in a multi-factor, multi-device security&nbsp;strategy.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">&nbsp;Challenges for the User Experience<\\/p>\\n<ul class=\\\"ul1\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"li1\\\">How can one get everyday users to do these complicated maneuvers?<\\/li>\\n<li class=\\\"li1\\\">Can we make this a fun and fast process?<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h3 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>The lean approach: Experiment and Learn&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Before building the security solution, we identified the two MVP experiments that the PhonePass team should run.<\\/p>\\n<ol class=\\\"ol1\\\">\\n<li class=\\\"li1\\\">Test whether the UX is delightful and effective in obtaining the results?<\\/li>\\n<li class=\\\"li1\\\">Test whether users can accomplish the task in a short time space, especially through repeated use?<\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Additionally, the PhonePass team decided to add another experiment: Test whether their implemented algorithm yields unique device fingerprints?<\\/p>\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_wrapper\\\">\\n<h3 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>The Solution<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">The most critical feature was to come up the alignment interaction: a way to guide users to align the device to only one of the X, Y and Z dimensions.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">Taking a cue from airplane horizon indicators, the elegant UX solution was to align the black border (which moves with one of the dimensions), the blue line (which moves with another dimension) with the red line which indicates the perfect center.<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">A similar approach was used for the horizontal plane but with overlapping bubbles.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000068.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_usage\\\" width=\\\"938\\\" height=\\\"975\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<div class=\\\"prk_shortcode-title prk_break_word pulse_left_align h3_sized\\\">\\n<p>A simple set of instructions told users what to do and vibration based feedback indicated when they had succeeded.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000067.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_instructions\\\" width=\\\"1280\\\" height=\\\"720\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<h3 class=\\\"header_font zero_color prk_vc_title\\\">The Gamification<\\/h3>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\"><span style=\\\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\\\">To motivate users to work this repeatedly and to provide enough statistical data for our experiments, we gamified the experiences and allowed users to compete against themselves in seeing how fast they could get all 6 readings done.<\\/span><\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\"><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000069.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_game\\\" width=\\\"837\\\" height=\\\"701\\\" \\/><\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<div class=\\\"clearfix\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\",\"banner_image\":null,\"thumbnail\":\"66\"}','{\"details\":\"<div class=\\\"prk_shortcode-title prk_break_word pulse_center_align h4_sized\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"header_font zero_color prk_vc_title\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \\\">\\n<div class=\\\"wpb_wrapper\\\">\\n<h2 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>PhonePass<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\n<h3 class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>How does one craft a User Experience for device orientations in 6 degrees of freedom?<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">PhonePass has a patent-pending algorithm to uniquely identify devices based on the hardware signature obtained by holding the device in six different very precise orientations &ndash; vertical facing you, vertical away from you, horizontal facing you, horizontal away from you, on its back, and on its face. The unique device determination is used in a multi-factor, multi-device 