ul>\\n<li>How can one get everyday users to do these complicated maneuvers?<\\/li>\\n<li>Can we make this a fun and fast process?<\\/li>\\n<li>The lean approach: Experiment and Learn&nbsp;<\\/li>\\n<li>Before building the security solution, we identified the two MVP experiments that the PhonePass team should run.<\\/li>\\n<li>Test whether the UX is delightful and effective in obtaining the results?<\\/li>\\n<li>Test whether users can accomplish the task in short time space, especially through repeated use?<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p>Additionally, the PhonePass team decided to add another experiment: Test whether their implemented algorithm yields unique device fingerprints?<\\/p>\\n<h3 class=\\\"project-section-title\\\">User Testing<\\/h3>\\n<p>After developing an initial prototype, we decided to test out the interactions. We gave this app out to different people, which included people who were already aware of the app and people who were not. We also went to the neighboring offices and asked complete strangers to use the app, while we observed how they went through the process and noted the points where they faced difficulty.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000143.png\\\" alt=\\\"user test\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"504\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>Just observing them made me learn a lot about how people handle phones, which way they tend to turn first, and the difference between how left handed people used it as opposed to the right-handed. We also paid attention to whether they bother reading the given instructions or do they depend more on quick imagery to guide them.<\\/p>\\n<h3>The Solution<\\/h3>\\n<p>The most critical feature was to come up the alignment interaction: a way to guide users to align the device to only one of the X, Y and Z dimensions.<\\/p>\\n<p>Taking a cue from airplane horizon indicators, the elegant UX solution was to align the black border (which moves with one of the dimensions), the blue line (which moves with another dimension) with the red line which indicates the perfect center.<\\/p>\\n<p>A similar approach was used for the horizontal plane but with overlapping bubbles.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000068.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_usage\\\" width=\\\"938\\\" height=\\\"975\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>A simple set of instructions told users what to do and vibration based feedback indicated when they had succeeded.<\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000144.png\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass flow\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"691\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<h3>The Gamification<\\/h3>\\n<p>To motivate users to work this repeatedly and to provide enough statistical data for our experiments, we gamified the experiences and allowed users to compete against themselves in seeing how fast they could get all 6 readings done.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000069.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"phonepass_game\\\" width=\\\"837\\\" height=\\\"701\\\" \\/><\\/p>\",\"id\":\"24\"}',NULL,NULL,1,'2019-06-12 10:11:33','192.168.0.1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_14_5) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/74.0.3729.169 Safari/537.36'),(490,'ENTRY','UPDATE','5','projects',5,1,'{\"id\":\"5\",\"status\":\"1\",\"sort\":\"3\",\"project_type_id\":\"2\",\"title\":\"enfold Digital Locker\",\"subtitle\":null,\"details\":\"<p>Enfold provides digital lockers that keep your documents safe, secure and always available. Enfold&rsquo;s digital lockers automatically obtain documents worth storing from your email accounts and web portals.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Brief<\\/h3>\\n<p>I received the Enfold project as a concept along with a basic implemented website that required some heavy remodeling, especially in terms of their UX. Their current website consisted of only the basic features of the product, and my project was to redesign it to include many more complex features, and to design them in a way that is understandable and usable by the mass people. I worked on this project for almost a year.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000014.jpg\\\" width=\\\"1000\\\" height=\\\"563\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000011.jpg\\\" width=\\\"1000\\\" height=\\\"569\\\" \\/>With a global strategy, the portal supports multiple languages and locales, in terms of the content on the pages, the content in any communications and incoming content. In addition, technically, it works on multiple cloud platforms and integrates with multiple email providers, SMS providers, and payment processors. A marketplace of additional products and services along with an advanced promotions campaign and subscription management supports a direct-to-consumer business model.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000037.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"img4 market pay\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"342\\\" \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>A rich set of APIs and webhooks allows the entire system to be integrated with external (or internal systems) including single sign-on, subscription, and payments, account life-cycle, locker state changes, depositing documents, sharing and more.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Approach<\\/h3>\\n<p>I started out by talking to the clients. I spoke especially to the owner of the product Mr. Inderjeet Gujral and tried to understand their approach towards the project along with some brainstorming over the UX of some of the new features. Understanding that they had a certain picture in mind, I started researching on the already existing products in the market that provide cloud storing solutions such as Dropbox and Google Drive and study the product to understand their approach to solving some common UX problems.<\\/p>\\n<h3 class=\\\"project-section-title\\\">Website Design<\\/h3>\\n<div class=\\\"text-section-center\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"main-text\\\">\\n<p>The initial process consisted of making the wireframes in Balsamiq and a frequent back and forth<\\/p>\\n<p>conversations and presentations with clients over Skype. It took about 3-4 months and<\\/p>\\n<p>approximately 10 iterations to get the initial pages to the coders and begin the development of<\\/p>\\n<p>the platform.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Wireframe<\\/h4>\\n<h4>UI Design<\\/h4>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<p>The system works in multiple modes &ndash; as a white label, fully branded offering, as a consumer-facing offering and as a co-branded offering. The entire architecture was baked by testing with an external security and penetration test.<\\/p>\\n<p>We planned a load and scale test to test this system to support 800 million lockers with a high degree of concurrent use scenarios. This load and scale test was verified by the cloud provider.<\\/p>\\n<h3>App Design<\\/h3>\\n<p>My challenge here was to sculpt an experience that would allow users to operate the complex features of their lockers on a much smaller screen. I started out by taking in the feedback that I was receiving on the website from the testers and beta users, which helped me in pointing out my initial mistakes. Keeping these in mind I started brainstorming with my team members and figuring out a way to further simplify the UX. Designing for smartphones, also meant that I had more information about the user that could be used to make the functioning of the app better.<\\/p>\\n<p>I decided to use Material Design for the visuals of the app, as having z-axis helped me logically layer the UI and make the complex interactions clearer. It also provided a large number of in-built components of the library that could be customized and used, which significantly saved upon development time.<\\/p>\\n<p>Unfortunately, due to some internal hurdles faced by the clients, the app hasn&rsquo;t made it to the app store or play store yet.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Additional Products<\\/h3>\\n<h4>MICROSOFT OUTLOOK AND OFFICE ADD-IN<\\/h4>\\n<p>The locker integrates with external tools such as the entire Microsoft office suite. Users of Office and Outlook can directly add or retrieve documents from the locker.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000096.png\\\" alt=\\\"outlook addin image2\\\" width=\\\"2594\\\" height=\\\"1546\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000036.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"img6 addin\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"360\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<h4>ADMIN PORTAL - TO MANAGE MULTIPLE LOCKER PORTALS<\\/h4>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000092.png\\\" alt=\\\"admin portal\\\" width=\\\"2602\\\" height=\\\"1558\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"banner_image\":\"9\",\"thumbnail\":\"89\"}','{\"details\":\"<p>Enfold provides digital lockers that keep your documents safe, secure and always available. Enfold&rsquo;s digital lockers automatically obtain documents worth storing from your email accounts and web portals.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Brief<\\/h3>\\n<p>I received the Enfold project as a concept along with a basic implemented website that required some heavy remodeling, especially in terms of their UX. Their current website consisted of only the basic features of the product, and my project was to redesign it to include many more complex features, and to design them in a way that is understandable and usable by the mass people. I worked on this project for almost a year.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000014.jpg\\\" width=\\\"1000\\\" height=\\\"563\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000011.jpg\\\" width=\\\"1000\\\" height=\\\"569\\\" \\/>With a global strategy, the portal supports multiple languages and locales, in terms of the content on the pages, the content in any communications and incoming content. In addition, technically, it works on multiple cloud platforms and integrates with multiple email providers, SMS providers, and payment processors. A marketplace of additional products and services along with an advanced promotions campaign and subscription management supports a direct-to-consumer business model.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000037.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"img4 market pay\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"342\\\" \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<p>A rich set of APIs and webhooks allows the entire system to be integrated with external (or internal systems) including single sign-on, subscription, and payments, account life-cycle, locker state changes, depositing documents, sharing and more.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Approach<\\/h3>\\n<p>I started out by talking to the clients. I spoke especially to the owner of the product Mr. Inderjeet Gujral and tried to understand their approach towards the project along with some brainstorming over the UX of some of the new features. Understanding that they had a certain picture in mind, I started researching on the already existing products in the market that provide cloud storing solutions such as Dropbox and Google Drive and study the product to understand their approach to solving some common UX problems.<\\/p>\\n<h3 class=\\\"project-section-title\\\">Website Design<\\/h3>\\n<div class=\\\"text-section-center\\\">\\n<div class=\\\"main-text\\\">\\n<p>The initial process consisted of making the wireframes in Balsamiq and a frequent back and forth<\\/p>\\n<p>conversations and presentations with clients over Skype. It took about 3-4 months and<\\/p>\\n<p>approximately 10 iterations to get the initial pages to the coders and begin the development of<\\/p>\\n<p>the platform.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Wireframe<\\/h4>\\n<h4>UI Design<\\/h4>\\n<\\/div>\\n<\\/div>\\n<p>The system works in multiple modes &ndash; as a white label, fully branded offering, as a consumer-facing offering and as a co-branded offering. The entire architecture was baked by testing with an external security and penetration test.<\\/p>\\n<p>We planned a load and scale test to test this system to support 800 million lockers with a high degree of concurrent use scenarios. This load and scale test was verified by the cloud provider.<\\/p>\\n<h3>App Design<\\/h3>\\n<p>My challenge here was to sculpt an experience that would allow users to operate the complex features of their lockers on a much smaller screen. I started out by taking in the feedback that I was receiving on the website from the testers and beta users, which helped me in pointing out my initial mistakes. Keeping these in mind I started brainstorming with my team members and figuring out a way to further simplify the UX. Designing for smartphones, also meant that I had more information about the user that could be used to make the functioning of the app better.<\\/p>\\n<p>I decided to use Material Design for the visuals of the app, as having z-axis helped me logically layer the UI and make the complex interactions clearer. It also provided a large number of in-built components of the library that could be customized and used, which significantly saved upon development time.<\\/p>\\n<p>Unfortunately, due to some internal hurdles faced by the clients, the app hasn&rsquo;t made it to the app store or play store yet.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Additional Products<\\/h3>\\n<h4>MICROSOFT OUTLOOK AND OFFICE ADD-IN<\\/h4>\\n<p>The locker integrates with external tools such as the entire Microsoft office suite. Users of Office and Outlook can directly add or retrieve documents from the locker.<\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000096.png\\\" alt=\\\"outlook addin image2\\\" width=\\\"2594\\\" height=\\\"1546\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000036.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"img6 addin\\\" width=\\\"625\\\" height=\\\"360\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<h4>ADMIN PORTAL - TO MANAGE MULTIPLE LOCKER PORTALS<\\/h4>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/storage\\/uploads\\/00000000092.png\\\" alt=\\\"admin portal\\\" width=\\\"2602\\\" height=\\\"1558\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"id\":\"5\"}',NULL,NULL,1,'2019-06-12 10:33:51','192.168.0.1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_14_5) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/74.0.3729.169 Safari/537.36'),(491,'FILES','ADD','1','directus_files',145,1,'{\"id\":\"145\",\"status\":\"1\",\"name\":\"