INSERT INTO `projects` VALUES (1,1,0,3,'TripHobo App','Trip Plans App','<h2 class=\"p1\">&nbsp;TripHobo: Trip Plans App</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>The user on the app should be able to \"Create a Plan, Manage their Plan and Explore other Trip Plans. All the features from the website like City details, An Attraction details, Country\'s page were not accessible from the app. This was supposed to be the first version of the app and hence not to be overloaded with everything.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>Sticking to UI guide of the website, minimal content but neatly placed for users to manage their plans through their phones. So nothing from the trip building tool was to be left out.</p>\n<p>Few in house testing with app designs carried out to understand the user\'s behavior and their expectations from the app.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;<img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000057.png\" alt=\"1 HomeScreen Login 1\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000056.png\" alt=\"1 HomeScreen Login 1b\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000055.png\" alt=\"0 Menu 1b\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000167.jpg\" alt=\"acco9 jpg\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000168.png\" alt=\"4  2 \" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000049.png\" alt=\"5d\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000052.png\" alt=\"1 hotel main\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000166.png\" alt=\"2 hotel listing\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000051.png\" alt=\"3 hotel detail\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000050.png\" alt=\"3 hotel detail b\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>',NULL,48),(2,1,9,3,'Exclusive','Social Gathering App','<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Brief</span></h3>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Exclusive is the Social Gathering App and wishes to transform the way people meet and hang out in the real world. The app was designed targeting to users living in the United States of America and Canada only. The app logo was also to be designed.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\">Approach&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>The app was to be designed to target teenagers specifically. The app had a profile handle with which the user can tag their friends and places to visit. The app had to be lively, easy to use, for the youth, so no formal messaging and boring theme strictly. Started with designing the logo after selecting the theme of the app.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000043.jpg\" alt=\"eux transformation 1 copy\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" /></p>',42,87),(3,0,1,3,'Nap26','Rest and Rejuvination',NULL,NULL,3),(4,1,2,1,'TripHobo Blog Ad',NULL,NULL,NULL,15),(5,1,3,2,'enfold Digital Locker',NULL,'<p>Enfold provides digital lockers that keep your documents safe, secure and always available. Enfold&rsquo;s digital lockers automatically obtain documents worth storing from your email accounts and web portals.</p>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>I received the Enfold project as a concept along with a basic implemented website that required some heavy remodeling, especially in terms of their UX. Their current website consisted of only the basic features of the product, and my project was to redesign it to include many more complex features, and to design them in a way that is understandable and usable by the mass people. I worked on this project for almost a year.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000014.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"563\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000011.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"569\" />With a global strategy, the portal supports multiple languages and locales, in terms of the content on the pages, the content in any communications and incoming content. In addition, technically, it works on multiple cloud platforms and integrates with multiple email providers, SMS providers, and payment processors. A marketplace of additional products and services along with an advanced promotions campaign and subscription management supports a direct-to-consumer business model.</p>\n<p>A rich set of APIs and webhooks allows the entire system to be integrated with external (or internal systems) including single sign-on, subscription, and payments, account life-cycle, locker state changes, depositing documents, sharing and more.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>I started out by talking to the clients. I spoke especially to the owner of the product and tried to understand their approach towards the project along with some brainstorming over the UX of some of the new features. Understanding that they had a certain picture in mind, I started researching on the already existing products in the market that provide cloud storing solutions such as Dropbox and Google Drive and study the product to understand their approach to solving some common UX problems.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000153.png\" alt=\"navigation (1)\" width=\"566\" height=\"734\" /></p>\n<h3 class=\"project-section-title\">Website Design</h3>\n<div class=\"text-section-center\">\n<div class=\"main-text\">\n<p>The initial process consisted of making the wireframes in Balsamiq and a frequent back and forth</p>\n<p>conversations and presentations with clients over Skype. It took about 3-4 months and</p>\n<p>approximately 10 iterations to get the initial pages to the coders and begin the development of</p>\n<p>the platform.</p>\n<h3>Wireframe</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000152.png\" alt=\"wireframes (1)\" width=\"1301\" height=\"922\" /></p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000149.png\" alt=\"ui image1 (1)\" width=\"1155\" height=\"771\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000151.png\" alt=\"ui image2 (1)\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000150.png\" alt=\"ui image3 (1)\" width=\"1156\" height=\"772\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The system works in multiple modes &ndash; as a white label, fully branded offering, as a consumer-facing offering and as a co-branded offering. The entire architecture was baked by testing with an external security and penetration test.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>We planned a load and scale test to test this system to support 800 million lockers with a high degree of concurrent use scenarios. This load and scale test was verified by the cloud provider.</p>\n<h3>App Design</h3>\n<p>My challenge here was to sculpt an experience that would allow users to operate the complex features of their lockers on a much smaller screen. I started out by taking in the feedback that I was receiving on the website from the testers and beta users, which helped me in pointing out my initial mistakes. Keeping these in mind I started brainstorming with my team members and figuring out a way to further simplify the UX. Designing for smartphones, also meant that I had more information about the user that could be used to make the functioning of the app better.</p>\n<p>I decided to use Material Design for the visuals of the app, as having z-axis helped me logically layer the UI and make the complex interactions clearer. It also provided a large number of in-built components of the library that could be customized and used, which significantly saved upon development time.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, due to some internal hurdles faced by the clients, the app hasn&rsquo;t made it to the app store or play store yet.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000145.png\" alt=\"appui image1 (1)\" width=\"2490\" height=\"1490\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000146.png\" alt=\"appui image2 (1)\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1488\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000147.png\" alt=\"appui image3 (1)\" width=\"2502\" height=\"1486\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000148.png\" alt=\"appui image4 (1)\" width=\"625\" height=\"372\" /></p>\n<h3>Additional Products</h3>\n<h4>MICROSOFT OUTLOOK AND OFFICE ADD-IN</h4>\n<p>The locker integrates with external tools such as the entire Microsoft office suite. Users of Office and Outlook can directly add or retrieve documents from the locker.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000096.png\" alt=\"outlook addin image2\" width=\"2594\" height=\"1546\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000036.jpg\" alt=\"img6 addin\" width=\"625\" height=\"360\" /></p>\n<h4>ADMIN PORTAL - TO MANAGE MULTIPLE LOCKER PORTALS</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000092.png\" alt=\"admin portal\" width=\"2602\" height=\"1558\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',9,89),(6,1,11,1,'TripHobo Oktoberfest Ad',NULL,'',NULL,16),(7,1,4,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (1)',NULL,'',NULL,17),(8,1,5,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (2)',NULL,'',NULL,18),(9,1,6,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (3)',NULL,'',NULL,19),(10,1,7,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (4)',NULL,'',NULL,20),(11,0,8,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (6)',NULL,'',NULL,21),(12,1,12,1,'TripHobo Oktoberfest Ad',NULL,'',NULL,22),(13,1,13,1,'Father\'s Day Ad Series',NULL,'',NULL,23),(14,1,14,1,'Father\'s Day Ad Series',NULL,'',NULL,24),(15,1,15,1,'Father\'s Day Ad Series',NULL,'',NULL,25),(16,1,10,1,'Travel Hacks Series Fb Post (5)',NULL,'',NULL,26),(17,2,NULL,1,'TripHobo Blog Ad (2)',NULL,'',NULL,27),(18,1,NULL,3,'Vendekin','Vending Machine App','<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>Vendekin is disrupting the vending machine ecosystem. They&rsquo;re introducing cashless payments, product upselling, operator efficiency,&nbsp;and brand engagement.</p>\n<p>I engaged with Vendekin to apply design thinking and craft a delightful user experience for the modern, consumer-facing vending app. Make the app fun, intuitive, and highly efficient thereby allowing people on-the-go to quickly and predictably complete their vending transactions.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>The design focused on addressing three main areas of user confusion.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Connect the app&nbsp;to a particular machine within seconds or sooner.</li>\n<li>Make the selection process clear and fun.</li>\n<li>Design around the confusion when dispensing beverages and multiple packaged goods.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Solution&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>A major area of confusion was preparing for beverage dispensation and collecting dispensed items&nbsp;especially when multiple items are purchased. Dispensation failures need to be handled immediately. For this reason, I paid special attention to our UX in this area. I designed around anticipated user behavior pitfalls without causing annoyance. Multiple other improvements enable upsell of products, brand engagement and support point in time promotions.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000035.jpg\" alt=\"vend img3\" width=\"1102\" height=\"801\" /></p>\n<p>The design makes it easy to instantly scan and connect to any machine. Furthermore, for frequently used machines, one-touch access provides an instant connection. To work around difficulties in scanning QR codes, a fallback option allows for easy entering of a PIN.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000034.jpg\" alt=\"vend img1\" width=\"1168\" height=\"791\" /><span style=\"font-family: verdana, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The design of the selection page provided a way to showcase branded products with large images. The selection is easy with just a simple plus (+) button. The major innovation is that selected items drop into a cart on the same screen resulting in instant confirmation and increased confidence in the selection.</span></p>\n<div class=\"gmail-wpb_wrapper\">&nbsp;</div>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000033.jpg\" alt=\"vend img 2\" width=\"770\" height=\"863\" /></p>',40,39),(19,1,NULL,2,'CUDDLY','Animal Welfare Website','<p>poundWISHES, now CUDDLY is an online crowdfunding platform that connects animal lovers with animal rescues and shelters. Technology is at the heart of the business. Ignite Solutions (my current workplace) are the UX &amp; technology partner for CUDDLY.</p>\n<p>Our first task was to stabilize the existing system. poundWISHES was handled by another firm earlier and we faced a lot of issues while working with the previous architecture and hence came up with a simple one-flow-at-a-time revamp plan.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I recommended a multi-phased UX improvement and modernizing approach. The web interface was revamped to give the site a fresh look. I established a detailed web and campaign tracking to give insights into donor behavior. Started emailers for donors, installed HotJar on the website to keep a track of user\'s behavior.</p>\n<p>Tighter and reliable integration with payment providers reduced reconciliation errors and streamlined the crowdfunding distribution.</p>\n<p>Embarked on a major initiative to bring in an innovative pet gift registry offering, the first of its kind. Donors could gift items to rescued pets rather than just cash. This offering has been a hit.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Working with CUDDLY to introduce new features and improvise the experience as we now have a comparatively stable system.</p>\n<p>The client wanted to highlight the new feature on the homepage \"adopter registries\" but it failed to make users understand what it used to do or still does along with registries. Came up with a design which is a page which will divert the three types of users of Cuddly: Pet Parents, Donors, and Rescues.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000075.jpg\" alt=\"homepage_cuddly\" width=\"625\" height=\"635\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Homepage designed to show what Cuddly is, what all it does for animal welfare without promoting any single module. Buttons for users to navigate to sub-landing pages. The purpose of this design was that CUDDLY stepped in \"registries\" along with donations and fundraising. One section celebrating the happiness and the other two were not joyful. To balance out these emotions, came up with a homepage which does not promote any module and gives equal space to Registries, Rescues, and Donors. Therefore, no navigation bar is added until the user selects one of the three buttons.</p>\n<p>Cuddly stepped into e-commerce business and there were few designs shared in the process.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000138.jpg\" alt=\"cuddly shop\" width=\"6238\" height=\"2115\" />&nbsp;Note: Cuddly is no more my client from 5 months now and whatever is on their live site isn\'t my contribution.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',45,44),(20,1,NULL,2,'CUDDLY','Adopter Registry Flow','<h2>CUDDLY Pet Registry</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>Design CUDDLY\'s pet registry flow for pet owners. CUDDLY needs to ask a few questions about the pet parent and their pet. Based on the answers provided, CUDDLYwould show products and product collections, tailored to your preferences. May it cute, fun and easy for the parents so they can answer more and more questions without stressing out.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>One question on each page to make it look cleaner with large font and input/options. Made a slider with the first two questions mandatory for the pet to be created in the database. Gave a light theme to the flow. The progress bar at the top to let the user know his journey and how far he is from completion. At any point, the user can skip and proceed to add items after mandatory questions and complete the quiz later for better recommendations. Reason solely being not to annoy the user.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000080.png\" alt=\"flow type\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000081.png\" alt=\"flow name\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000082.png\" alt=\"flow gender\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000083.png\" alt=\"flow images\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000085.png\" alt=\"8 size\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000084.png\" alt=\"6 about adopter\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000086.png\" alt=\"11 description\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1024\" /></p>\n<h3>Shop Experience</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000179.jpg\" alt=\"cuddly shop\" width=\"3041\" height=\"2115\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000180.jpg\" alt=\"cuddly shop copy\" width=\"625\" height=\"409\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',46,91),(21,1,NULL,2,'CUDDLY','Blog','<h2>CUDDLY Blog</h2>\n<p>CUDDLY wanted to revamp their blog design incorporating PetCo ads. The new blog design for CUDDLY was a challenge. Giving more emphasis on the images, easy subscription form in the right sidebar and in-house ads to convert the traffic to donations and registries.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000070.jpg\" alt=\"blog_basic\" width=\"1859\" height=\"1280\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Two styles of blog articles are published on Cuddly Blog, one being slider based. Added slideshow with play pause buttons to make it easy for the user to go through a lot of images.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000071.jpg\" alt=\"blog_advance\" width=\"640\" height=\"336\" /></p>',NULL,63),(22,0,NULL,2,'BooksPlus','Wordpress Website','<p>BooksPlus uses the power of augmented reality to bring printed pages to life. Just scan images in the book using the BooksPlus app and get immersed in rich, interactive content. Reading was never this much fun.</p>',NULL,64),(23,0,NULL,3,'BooksPlus','Augmented Reality App','',NULL,65),(24,1,NULL,3,'PhonePass',NULL,'<h2>PhonePass</h2>\n<h3><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">Brief</span></h3>\n<p>This was one of the very interesting projects that I worked on during my time at Ignite Solutions. It was a tight budget project, it needed to be completed in 50 hours.</p>\n<p>The clients were working on an algorithm that could uniquely identify a device based on the figures received from the accelerometer of the phone. They wanted us to come up with a beta product which would help them test out their theory. The challenge was that they needed a unique experience which would make the users turn their phones in different directions so that they could record the readings.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>We started out interacting with the clients, reading up the docs they sent and getting into Skype meetings with them, trying to understand what they need the user to do and how exactly did they see this product working. Since this was a new concept, the only way to research was to quickly create a prototype and test it. We stormed through various ideas, from pouring water in a glass to docking a spaceship. But since this was just a beta prototype, we needed to do something simple and straightforward.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000142.png\" alt=\"approach\" width=\"625\" height=\"592\" /></p>\n<p>We decided to experiment with simple alignment interaction, where the user had to move the phone in order to align shapes on the phone. We took reference from the Apple leveling app and tried to turn the whole thing into a simple game that people could enjoy and at the same time give us the required metrics.</p>\n<h3 class=\"project-section-title white-text\">UX and UI Design</h3>\n<div class=\"main-text\">\n<p>The UX is simple, align the blue line and black border to the red line, which represents the horizon.</p>\n<p>But here&rsquo;s the catch, tilting the phone left or right also tilts the blue line, and tilting the phone back</p>\n<p>and forth moved the black border. So in order to align the lines, the phone has to be held straight</p>\n<p>in a certain direction. Following through six steps, i.e six directions completes the exercise.</p>\n</div>\n<h3><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">Challenges for the User Experience</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>How can one get everyday users to do these complicated maneuvers?</li>\n<li>Can we make this a fun and fast process?</li>\n<li>The lean approach: Experiment and Learn&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Before building the security solution, we identified the two MVP experiments that the PhonePass team should run.</li>\n<li>Test whether the UX is delightful and effective in obtaining the results?</li>\n<li>Test whether users can accomplish the task in short time space, especially through repeated use?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additionally, the PhonePass team decided to add another experiment: Test whether their implemented algorithm yields unique device fingerprints?</p>\n<h3 class=\"project-section-title\">User Testing</h3>\n<p>After developing an initial prototype, we decided to test out the interactions. We gave this app out to different people, which included people who were already aware of the app and people who were not. We also went to the neighboring offices and asked complete strangers to use the app, while we observed how they went through the process and noted the points where they faced difficulty.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000143.png\" alt=\"user test\" width=\"625\" height=\"504\" /></p>\n<p>Just observing them made me learn a lot about how people handle phones, which way they tend to turn first, and the difference between how left handed people used it as opposed to the right-handed. We also paid attention to whether they bother reading the given instructions or do they depend more on quick imagery to guide them.</p>\n<h3>The Solution</h3>\n<p>The most critical feature was to come up the alignment interaction: a way to guide users to align the device to only one of the X, Y and Z dimensions.</p>\n<p>Taking a cue from airplane horizon indicators, the elegant UX solution was to align the black border (which moves with one of the dimensions), the blue line (which moves with another dimension) with the red line which indicates the perfect center.</p>\n<p>A similar approach was used for the horizontal plane but with overlapping bubbles.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000068.jpg\" alt=\"phonepass_usage\" width=\"938\" height=\"975\" /></p>\n<p>A simple set of instructions told users what to do and vibration based feedback indicated when they had succeeded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000144.png\" alt=\"phonepass flow\" width=\"625\" height=\"691\" /></p>\n<h3>The Gamification</h3>\n<p>To motivate users to work this repeatedly and to provide enough statistical data for our experiments, we gamified the experiences and allowed users to compete against themselves in seeing how fast they could get all 6 readings done.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000069.jpg\" alt=\"phonepass_game\" width=\"837\" height=\"701\" /></p>',NULL,66),(25,1,NULL,2,'Zilkr',NULL,'<h2>Zilkr:&nbsp;<strong>PRO-ACTIVE CRM</strong></h2>\n<h3 class=\"p1\">Brief</h3>\n<p class=\"p1\">Zilkr builds platforms that API-enable an enterprise&rsquo;s telecom network. Requests and events in the telecom network, such as incoming calls, messages or outgoing calls, can now be integrated with Internet-based services.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000074.jpg\" alt=\"Zilkr notification\" width=\"1280\" height=\"850\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Zilkr came to get help conceptualize what such an integrated phone and desktop experience could look like. Furthermore, Zilkr wanted to explore what such an experience would require from a technology protocol perspective to allow 3rd party apps to execute in the Zilkr framework.</p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\">Approach</h3>\n<p>Rather than jump into this from a UX design perspective, I applied a design thinking approach to balance the business needs of Zilkr, the user&rsquo;s expectations and intuitive interfaces and the technology protocol that would sustain such a framework for 3rd party developed apps</p>\n<p>A round of wireframes was done before the UI Design.</p>\n<h3>Wireframe</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000154.jpg\" alt=\"zilkr wire\" width=\"1267\" height=\"704\" /></p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000155.jpg\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 06 12 at 4.30.23 PM\" width=\"1355\" height=\"551\" /></p>\n<p>I developed a dynamic,<strong><em> <a href=\"https://youtu.be/t55wp8TpVRQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">interactive prototype</a> </em></strong>that demonstrated all aspects of the user stories.</p>\n<p>Zilkr was successful in taking this interactive prototype to their customers and getting traction for a new offering.&nbsp;</p>',NULL,72),(26,1,NULL,2,'TripHobo','Travel Planner','<h2 class=\"p1\">TripHobo</h2>\n<h3 class=\"p1\">Brief</h3>\n<p class=\"p1\">TripHobo is an innovative&nbsp;trip planning platform&nbsp;that enables users to plan trips from over 90,000 cities across the world. TripHobo&rsquo;s trip planning platform serves as a one-stop destination for all the travel needs- exploring attractions, creating itineraries and booking hotels, transportation, and tours.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Users should be able to book their hotels, transportation, and tours from the portal. Propagate the thought of simple and care-free travel.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000077.jpg\" alt=\"triphobo website\" width=\"625\" height=\"398\" /></p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\">Approach&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>The first fold of each page should have all the important information from a user\'s point of view.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>City details (Best time to visit, how to travel to the city, how to roam around in the city, etc.)</li>\n<li>An Attraction\'s/Place to See details (Opening and Closing timings, ticket price, time to explore the place, etc.)</li>\n<li>Tour details (price, timings and booking call to action button)</li>\n<li>Hotel details (room fare, availability, hotel/room images, few common amenities)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<h4>Homepage</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000158.jpg\" alt=\"3 tab homepage tours 1200 980\" width=\"624\" height=\"1371\" /></p>\n<h4>Tours Booking</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000159.png\" alt=\"2 tours lisitng page\" width=\"625\" height=\"849\" /></p>\n<h4>Blog</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000165.jpg\" alt=\"1 blog design 2016 v2\" width=\"623\" height=\"1606\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,76),(27,1,NULL,3,'NAP26','Sleep, Recharge, Rejuvenate','<h2>NAP26</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>This audio program which uses pulsating beats to create sound vibration which matches natural sleeping patterns, signaling the brain to enter a more relaxed state. NAP26 will wake you after 26 minutes, researched as the optimum length of time for a power nap. <em>The project was on a tight budget and hence no wireframing nor prototyping was developed for the client.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000078.jpg\" alt=\"Nap 26\" width=\"1280\" height=\"583\" /></p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>Moving on, I started working on the art direction I wanted to take for the product. I researched some examples out there in the market and created style tiles that would help me move forward.</p>\n<p>Considering the fact that my users may be in a sensitive state of mind, I wanted the color options to be lively and uplifting but at the same time not too over-powering. The hue option is towards the cooler tone inducing a calm feeling while still being trendy enough so that my target audience can relate to it.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p>Not only the app design but the logo was also designed by me. A few of the variations of the logo were sent to the client to choose from.</p>\n<h4>Onboarding Screen</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000156.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 06 12 at 9.50.48 PM\" width=\"625\" height=\"284\" /></p>\n<h4>In-App Experience (iOS+Android)</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000157.png\" alt=\"napall\" width=\"915\" height=\"840\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,79),(28,1,NULL,3,'PhonePass Phase 2',NULL,'<h2>PhonePass Phase 2</h2>\n<p>PhonePass has a patent-pending algorithm to uniquely identify devices based on the hardware signature obtained by holding the device in six different very precise orientations &ndash; vertical facing you, vertical away from you, horizontal facing you, horizontal away from you, on its back, and on its face. The unique device determination is used in a multi-factor, multi-device security&nbsp;strategy. They came back to us for phase 2 designing. The UI was more modern and the high-quality illustrations used.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000125.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.19.41 PM\" width=\"1948\" height=\"572\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000126.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.27.55 PM\" width=\"625\" height=\"220\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000127.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.28.08 PM\" width=\"1437\" height=\"505\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000128.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.28.22 PM\" width=\"1378\" height=\"606\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,97),(29,1,NULL,3,'BooksPlus - Augmented Reality',NULL,'<h2>BooksPlus</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>Brings the power of Augmented Reality (AR) to printed books. Just scan the images in books and get immersed in rich, interactive content.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>Created a <strong><em><a href=\"https://www.booksplusapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">WordPress Website</span></a></em></strong> for users to understand what the product is about. Started with Scan screen, 5 of featured book listing and All Books listing. Keeping scan as the landing screen after splash screen was let the user start with scanning without hunting for the \"scan\" button on other screens.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000181.png\" alt=\"scan bp\" width=\"374\" height=\"669\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000182.png\" alt=\"bp featured\" width=\"373\" height=\"669\" /></p>\n<p>Following are the templates in which a publisher can publish/show their content after an image is scanned from their book.</p>\n<p><strong>Music Player, Audio Gallery, Video Gallery, and Factoid.</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000186.png\" alt=\"audio1\" width=\"368\" height=\"666\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000187.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.39.05 PM\" width=\"372\" height=\"664\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000188.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.39.14 PM\" width=\"377\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000190.png\" alt=\"gallery2\" width=\"625\" height=\"350\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000189.png\" alt=\"gallery1\" width=\"625\" height=\"353\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000132.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 05 22 at 4.44.39 PM\" width=\"1437\" height=\"809\" /></p>\n<p><br /><br /></p>',NULL,129),(30,1,NULL,2,'InGeST - Invoice Extraction',NULL,'<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">InGeST</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Extract intelligence from invoices.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Easily forward invoices via email or scans.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Easy classification of the extracted content.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Export to accounting ready formats. It is a concept by Ignite Solutions and we are building the product and improvising on the technology.</span></p>\n<p><img style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000135.png\" alt=\"ingest cover copy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000136.jpg\" alt=\"ingest cover copy 2\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /></span></p>\n<p><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>',NULL,137),(31,1,NULL,2,'Machine Cover : Cyber Warranties',NULL,'<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Machine Cover </span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Web-scale, multi-tenant, multi-lingual architecture.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">Scans millions of sites several times a day.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Machine learning to predict site performance.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Online purchase of warranties.</span></p>\n<p><strong>I have signed an NDA with the client, therefore cannot display the designs here. If asked about the product during the interview I will be able to talk briefly about it.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,141),(32,1,NULL,2,'Priv8Pay','Claim Company Expenses','<h2>Priv8Pay</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>An app for the corporate to claim their company expenses: Travel, Tour, Receipts and Bills via a corporate app. An admin portal for the app to be managed.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>Receipt scanning using OCR introduced, so maximum data is prefilled after the user scans the receipt. The fields which could not be read via OCR, have editable fields so the user can add details.</p>\n<p>The receipt/expense has to be assigned to the reporting manager. The manager has a different view where he can manage his and his teams\' expenses.</p>\n<p>An in app-notification and push notification when there is an update on submitted expense.</p>\n<p>Cases such as the reporting manager is out of office, the Manager can assign a temporary manager to his team who will get new expense requests. If an expense is rejected or incomplete a provision to choose from a list of reasons and also the manager could type custom response to the claim.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The App is still under the designing phase, but a backend is created for the Admin to manage the software.</p>\n<h3>Web App UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000175.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 06 12 at 11.25.55 PM\" width=\"1368\" height=\"838\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000176.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019 06 12 at 11.26.06 PM\" width=\"1362\" height=\"841\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,174),(33,1,NULL,2,'BooksPlus','Self Service Portal','<h2>BooksPlus Self Service Portal for Publishers</h2>\n<h3>Brief</h3>\n<p>Build a portal for the Publishers to add their content and link it with enhanced content and publish it to the app for the readers.</p>\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<p>Keeping in mind that the Publishers might or might now be tech-savvy, therefore, each page/action has content explaining what this page would do for them. Adding labels and with the help of visuals making the users understand how it would look after publishing in the app. Helping Publishers with current and previously published content in their dashboard. Clean design to help focus the user.</p>\n<h3>UI Design</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000193.jpg\" alt=\"Home\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000194.jpg\" alt=\"Project.Empty\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000195.jpg\" alt=\"Project.Hover\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000196.jpg\" alt=\"Trigger\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000197.jpg\" alt=\"Trigger.Add\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000198.jpg\" alt=\"Trigger.Factoid\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000199.jpg\" alt=\"Trigger.Factoid Filled\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"/storage/uploads/00000000200.jpg\" alt=\"Trigger.Quiz\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,192);
